instruction:
Given the length of a circumference. Find the radius of this circumference.

Set the variable `length` and assign it a value of an arbitrary non-negative number (the length of the circumference).

Set the variable `pi` and assign it a value of 3.14 (an approximate value of Pi).

Set the variable `radius`, in which you calculate the radius (to find the radius, divide the length of the circumference by 2 * Pi).

Here is an example that is fundamentally similar to what needs to be done, but adapt it to the requirements of the task:
```javascript
const l = 10;
const a = 3;
const r = l / (2 * a);

```

hint:
```javascript
const length = 10;
const pi = 3.14;
const radius = length / (2 * pi);
```
